# Testing Standards

## Purpose
Provide confidence through targeted, layered verification.

## Requirements
- test changed behavior first
- include unhappy-path and edge-case checks
- verify public contracts, not just internal implementation
- add regression coverage for fixed bugs where practical
- separate unit, integration, and end-to-end scope clearly
- test cross-layer assumptions when a task spans UI, API, graph, or LLM behavior
- report gaps and residual risks explicitly

## Apply When
- validating a fix or feature
- preparing release confidence checks
- reviewing contract changes
